place.name: TWYFORD
place.gazetteerText: TWYFORD, a parish in Mitford district, Norfolk; 2¾ miles NE by N of Elmham r. station. Post town, Foulham, under Thetford. Acres, 529. Real property, £1,173. Pop., 60. Houses, 14. The manor, with T. Hall, belongs to Mrs. Packe. The living is a rectory in the diocese of Norwich. Value, £148. Patron, the Rev. J. N. Spurgeon. The church is good. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
